1
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:24,840
Here

2
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,700
is the famous Malacca Chinatown.

3
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:27,680
And

4
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,000
for Malaysian Chinese,

5
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,400
the most important day of the year is the New Year.

6
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,600
So these decorations

7
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:33,920
represent the Malaysian Chinese's

8
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,380
love for Chinese culture.

9
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:37,610
Let's go.

10
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:39,530
Let's go.

11
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,380
Do I really have to?

12
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,520
Just try it.

13
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,640
I'd rather not.

14
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,079
Are you really not going to try it?

15
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:35,480
No.

16
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,680
I really can't get used to this smell.

17
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:42,500
There's a first time for everything.

18
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,480
Try it.

19
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:44,480
Next time.

20
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,840
Right now.

21
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,200
Boss.

22
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:49,810
Here.

23
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,570
Thank you, boss.

24
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,100
Do you really not want any?

25
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,320
Look, even Justin doesn't want any.

26
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:13,160
Justin,

27
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,720
do you really not want any?

28
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,320
Never mind. I don't want any.

29
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,760
Aren't you Malaysian?

30
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:20,960
Only in this regard,

31
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,680
I am super un-Malaysian.

32
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:25,360
See?

33
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,240
All right.

34
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,090
Try some.

35
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,450
How is it?

36
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:53,560
Not bad.

37
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,530
It's better than I thought.

38
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:56,960
Try this again.

39
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:57,520
Again?

40
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,240
Eat this piece. Here.

41
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,640
How is it? Delicious, right?

42
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,600
It's okay.

43
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,480
I like it here.

44
00:04:40,159 --> 00:04:40,960
What's wrong?

45
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,600
You could have told me.

46
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,850
I'm fine with it.

47
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,640
Tell you what?

48
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:03,240
Mr. Zeng invited you here

49
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,000
not just to help them repair porcelain.

50
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:11,120
He also wants you to stay here as an exchange student.

51
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,050
How did you know?

52
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,760
There's more room for development here

53
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,820
and a bigger stage.

54
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:18,400
Even though

55
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,660
we might not see each other for two years.

56
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,680
But I believe

57
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,930
as long as we still miss each other,

58
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,260
this distance and time won't stop us.

59
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,960
If you don't like me anymore,

60
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,260
I respect your choice.

61
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,200
As long as you choose

62
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,360
the path you prefer.

63
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,760
They all told me to be a bit selfish,

64
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,840
think of myself,

65
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,770
and ask you not to go.

66
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,900
After thinking about it, I still feel

67
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,480
I should respect your choice

68
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,160
because it's your own life.

69
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,560
But I don't want you to leave.

70
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,520
When did I ever say I was leaving you?

71
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,850
What did you say?

72
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,240
I've already rejected Mr. Zeng.

73
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,330
I won't stay here

74
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:32,300
because

75
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:36,840
without you here,

76
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,800
there's no point in staying.

77
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,200
What else are you asking?

78
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,380
What else did they say?

79
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,080
Nothing.

80
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,060
There are scholarships and a stage here.

81
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,000
From the very beginning, I felt...

82
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:56,730
Without you,

83
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,840
no matter how good the conditions or how big the stage,

84
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,100
it means nothing to me.

85
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,640
I won't stay alone in Malacca,

86
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,700
a place so far away.

87
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,560
What if someone else takes you away?

88
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,900
What if you fall for someone else?

89
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,090
Then what would I do?

90
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:26,010
You've been talking to yourself this whole time.

91
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,660
I don't need you to respect my choices like this.

92
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:33,340
I just need you to need me, and that's enough.

93
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,250
Xiaocen.

94
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,720
I won't leave you.

95
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,340
You will always be in my story.

96
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,280
Xu,

97
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,600
about the exchange program,

98
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:33,080
are you really not going to reconsider?

99
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:37,280
Thank you for your kindness.

100
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,659
But I've still decided

101
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,760
to stay and study in Jingdezhen.

102
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,320
All right.

103
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,520
Since you've made up your minds,

104
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,120
I won't push it.

105
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,160
Xu,

106
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,250
Xiaocen,

107
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,440
I want to show you something.

108
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:00,920
Here.

109
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:07,700
This is a blue-and-white porcelain vase from the Zhizheng reign.

110
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,880
The decoration is of dragons in seawater.

111
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,480
The color is rich and bright.

112
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,770
If I'm not mistaken,

113
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:14,920
this is a piece

114
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:18,440
from the imperial kiln of Jingdezhen in the Yuan Dynasty.

115
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,840
Blue-and-white porcelain from the Yuan Dynasty is very rare,

116
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,900
let alone this one you have, Mr. Zeng.

117
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,090
Although the body is a bit damaged,

118
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,900
it is still very precious.

119
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,320
To get it,

120
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,360
I really went to a lot of trouble.

121
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:34,640
Xu,

122
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,320
can you complete

123
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,680
the restoration of this porcelain?

124
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,340
Given my current skill level,

125
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,320
it would be quite difficult for me

126
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,920
to restore this piece alone.

127
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,440
I'd still need a more skilled restorer

128
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,600
like Mr. Yue

129
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,730
to help me finish it.

130
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,640
I thought so too.

131
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,080
Therefore, I've decided

132
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:57,960
to donate this piece to Jingdezhen Ceramic University

133
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:01,760
for your university to restore and collect.

134
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,720
You want to donate such a valuable piece of porcelain

135
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,520
to our school?

136
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:10,090
This piece originally came from Jingdezhen.

137
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,320
It ended up abroad

138
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,160
because it was

139
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:14,520
illegally salvaged.

140
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:18,000
I'm just returning it to its rightful owner.

141
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,200
But Mr. Zeng,

142
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,320
you spent so much money and effort

143
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,080
on this.

144
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,800
Are you just going to donate it to us?

145
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,320
I think returning to its homeland

146
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,840
is its best destination.

147
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,760
I used to worry that young people in China

148
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,520
wouldn't value this cultural heritage.

149
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,850
But seeing your passion

150
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:39,320
and professionalism in cultural relics restoration

151
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,460
has touched me.

152
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,080
Knowing there are still young people like you

153
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,040
in China

154
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,970
inheriting traditional culture,

155
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,520
I feel reassured.

156
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,040
I believe

157
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,010
you will take good care of them.

158
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:58,920
Xu Xiao,

159
00:10:59,240 --> 00:10:59,800
Xiaocen.

160
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,180
I won't see you out.

161
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:03,760
Thank you for your hospitality during this time.

162
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,680
You're welcome.

163
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,940
You helped me restore so much porcelain.

164
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,640
I should be the one thanking you.

165
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,200
It was our honor, Mr. Zeng.

166
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,600
Thank you for your hard work.

167
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,440
As for the cultural relic I donated,

168
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,040
I have entrusted a transport company

169
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,640
to deliver it to Jingdezhen.

170
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,440
Your school has already received it.

171
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,520
I'll leave its restoration to you.

172
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,360
Okay.

173
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,480
Rest assured, leave it to us.

174
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,600
We'll be taking our leave now.

175
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,200
Thank you.

176
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:28,440
Thank you.

177
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,000
Please visit Malaysia again.

178
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,260
Come visit us in China.

179
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,200
Okay.

180
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,690
We'll get going now.

181
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,320
Bye.

182
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:34,800
Bye.

183
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,440
Bye.

184
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,010
Goodbye.

185
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:36,840
Bye.

186
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:39,880
Bye.

187
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,800
Bye.

188
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:41,800
Bye.

189
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,200
Xu Xiao.

190
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:07,520
Mr. Zeng told me everything about you.

191
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,000
He is very satisfied with your work.

192
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,500
Thank you, Mr. Yue.

193
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,760
And you, Xiaocen.

194
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,970
I can't believe you went to Malaysia by yourself.

195
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,840
Mr. Zeng is also

196
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,210
very satisfied with your work.

197
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,880
You impressed him.

198
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,200
Really?

199
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:28,400
Xu Xiao.

200
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:31,240
I heard you gave up the opportunity

201
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,980
to be an exchange student.

202
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,370
I've disappointed you.

203
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:36,280
Actually,

204
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,640
I didn't want you to be an exchange student.

205
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:40,840
Such a good prospect,

206
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:43,700
who would want to let someone else teach you?

207
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,400
By the way,

208
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,800
The porcelain donated by Mr. Zeng

209
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:50,890
has arrived.

210
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,320
I checked its damage

211
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:55,200
and made a restoration plan.

212
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,040
Are you two

213
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,690
interested in joining?

214
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,040
Of course.

215
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:03,560
Good.

216
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,170
It's a deal then.

217
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:07,720
However,

218
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,080
the injury on my hand hasn't healed yet.

219
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,740
I can't participate in the restoration.

220
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,540
Mr. Yue, what should we do?

221
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:17,600
It's nothing.

222
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,170
You should know,

223
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,100
in Jingdezhen,

224
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,090
there is another expert

225
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,640
who has a deeper study

226
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,320
of blue-and-white porcelain.

227
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,080
Xu.

228
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:53,520
Xiao.

229
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:56,920
Xu.

230
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,200
Yue, long time no see.

231
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,160
Long time no see.

232
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:01,800
How is it?

233
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:03,000
Come on.

234
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,600
Let's have a look.

235
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,160
By the way, Xu.

236
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,040
The two young people I mentioned

237
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,400
are Xu Xiao and Xiaocen.

238
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,560
Dad,

239
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:22,680
why do you use tea water to mix this pigment?

240
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,560
When we mix the pigment,

241
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,680
it's best to use tea water that's been sitting for about a week.

242
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:28,880
Because at this time,

243
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:31,000
the tea water can fully ferment.

244
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,320
After fermentation,

245
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:34,080
when the pigment mixes with water,

246
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:35,740
it won't easily precipitate.

247
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,840
And it can slow down the speed

248
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,320
of it entering the surface of the body.

249
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,880
It makes it easier for us to draw

250
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:43,880
on the body later.

251
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,920
Once we lay the foundation

252
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,880
and finish outlining the lines,

253
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,440
we will need to use a water-separating pen.

254
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,490
Doesn't it look like a big rooster's beak?

255
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:55,480
It does.

256
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,720
This is called a chicken-head brush, got it?

257
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,600
Then we use it for coloring.

258
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:02,640
Dad, how do you know so much?

259
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,920
Who do you think your dad is?

260
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,480
When it comes to studying blue-and-white porcelain,

261
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:10,160
I am the best in Jingdezhen.

262
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:11,600
Dad.

263
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:13,040
When I grow up,

264
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:15,160
I want to be as amazing as you.

265
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,930
You will definitely be like me.

266
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,250
And you will do even better than me.

267
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,140
Good night.

268
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:16,740
Good night.

269
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:20,360
I'm off.

270
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:23,200
Bye.

271
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:35,400
Old Xu,

272
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,200
you've kept your skills sharp.

273
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:40,760
You even keep up with the times.

274
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,720
Good for you.

275
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,200
To be honest,

276
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,640
after all these years,

277
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,800
I never dared

278
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,560
to let my skills slip.

279
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:49,600
Of course,

280
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,280
it's mostly because of this kid.

281
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:53,720
It was Xiao

282
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,520
who pulled me back to a normal state.

283
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,080
I want to state my position.

284
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:02,080
In the future, whenever you need me,

285
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,360
I am duty-bound

286
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,690
and will definitely do my best.

287
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,400
Lao Xu,

288
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:09,930
isn't that why we asked you here this time?

289
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,660
We wouldn't leave you out.

290
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:14,839
Mr. Yue,

291
